1: Depending on your server set up, the following files and folders need to have chmod values of 644, 664 or 666 for files, and 755, 775 or 777 for folders:
	/install
	/install/install1.php
	/install/install2.php
	/install/install3.php
	/install/install4.php
	/archive
	/archive/attachment
	/images
	/images/avatars
	/images/avatars/uploads
	/configuration

2: Go to the root of your website and follow the install instructions. Example, http://www.example.com

3: Delete the install folder and all files wilthin it.

4: chmod /configuration directory to either 644, 664 or 666.